						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the compound of the Rājēśvara temple opposite to Rāmā's shrine.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">11th century A.D.</hi> </p>						

						<p>This is a damaged and incomplete record. The purport of the epitaph is not clear and the names (Sā)simayya and Śāntībhatāra can be made out.</p>						

						<p>In the date potion only the first two figures-98 can be made out. It belongs to the 11th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
